casebody.data:
MOTION AND PROCEDURAL RULINGS

2006-0989. State ex rel. Brown v. Bernard.

In Mandamus and Prohibition. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of mandamus and prohibition. Upon consideration of relator’s motion to expedite a ruling on the issuance of an alternative writ of prohibition,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the motion is denied.
